FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - MALAWI: OIE
********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: 7 May 2004
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <arodriguezm@SaludFMV.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information Vol 17- No. 19 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_46.HTM#Sec5>


Foot and mouth disease in Malawi in the northern region
-----------------------------------------------
Emergency report.

Information received on 5 May 2004 from Dr. Danny Oswald Chinombo, Deputy
Director of the Department of Animal Health and Industry, Ministry of
Agriculture and Livestock Development, Lilongwe.

Date of the report: 5 May 2004.

Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.

Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 22 Mar 2004.

Estimated date of primary infection: 16 Mar 2004.

Outbreaks:

Location: image available at:
<http://www.oie.int/cartes/MWI1.doc>

Karonga Agricultural Development Division, Chitipa district, Chiwanga dip
tank (9o 28' S - 33o 00' E)

No. of outbreaks: 1

Description of affected population: the affected population is mainly
smallholder beef cattle.

Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species / susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered

bov / 1306 / 22 / 0 / 0 / 0

Diagnosis:

A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Botswana Vaccine Institute (OIE
Reference Laboratory for foot and mouth disease).

B. Diagnostic tests used: ELISA (1) and cell culture. The results were
received on 16 Apr 2004.

C. Causal agent: virus serotype SAT 2.

Epidemiology:

A. Source of agent/origin of infection: the disease is believed to have
spread from Tunduma in Tanzania.

B. Mode of spread: the disease has been transmitted through contact.

C. Other epidemiological details: Chiwanga dip tank is the only confirmed
focus of the outbreak. 4 more dip tanks in the same district are at threat
from cases reported inside Tanzania. See map:
<http://www.oie.int/cartes/MWI1.doc>

These 4 dip tanks are:

Mukoma (9o 28' S - 33o 07' E) with 1666 cattle
Nyondo (9o 30' S - 33o 14' E) with 2155 cattle
Kapenda (9o 30' S - 33o 16' E) with 3090 cattle
Upighu (9o 30' S - 33o 20' E) with 1721 cattle

Control measures:

Vaccination is under way to contain the spread of the outbreak, zoning,
quarantine, movement control inside the country.

(1) ELISA: enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay

